OL,3,C'It was horrific': UK hair transplant
OL,4,Cpatients left disfigured and scarred
OL,6,FThe industry body has warned against
OL,7,Fcheap procedures advertised on social
OL,8,Fmedia being carried out by
OL,9,F'unlicensed' providers, leading many
OL,10,Fpatients to fork out thousands of
OL,11,Fpounds to have the procedure fixed.
OL,13,FA 60-year-old man in Kent says he
OL,14,Fopted to have a hair transplant done
OL,15,Fin the UK, believing it would be safer
OL,16,Fand more regulated than overseas.
OL,18,FBut he now says he wished he had never
OL,19,Fgone to the practice he did after two
OL,20,Ffailed surgeries.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
